{"word":"H4022 - מֶגֶד - meged - meh'-ghed - Pleasant","slug":"H4022","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מֶגֶד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>meged"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>meh'-ghed"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Pleasant"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05D2;&#x05D3; - meged</b> - <i>meh'-ghed</i><p/>From an unused root properly meaning to <i>be eminent</i>; properly a <i>distinguished</i> thing; hence something <i>valuable</i>, as a product or fruit: - pleasant, precious fruit (thing)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4025\">H4025</a>, <a href=\"#/H4030\">H4030</a>, <a href=\"#/H4047\">H4047</a>"}]}